  <static seed="1107" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/FractionArithmetic/MultiplyFractions40.pg">
    <statement><p>Multiply: <m>\displaystyle{-\frac{12}{5} \cdot \frac{5}{9}}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="9" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-{\frac{4}{3}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To multiply two fractions, multiply both numerators and both denominators. Don<rsq/>t forget to reduce the fraction if possible.</p>
<p>Remember: a positive number times a negative number is a negative number.</p>
<p>We have:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
    -\frac{12}{5} \cdot \frac{5}{9}
    \amp =-\frac{4\cdot3}{5} \cdot \frac{5}{3\cdot3} \\
    \amp =-\frac{4}{5} \cdot \frac{5}{3}\\ 
    \amp = -\frac{4}{3} 
    \end{aligned}}</m></p>
</solution>
